    Create Empty Internal List

    create_empty_list.Rd

    Creates an empty internal list of predefined structure. The list will subsequently be filled while the function fit_panel_sem is running.

    Usage

    create_empty_list(verbose)

    Arguments

    verbose

    Integer number describing verbosity of console output. 0...no output (default); 1...user messages; 2...debugging-relevant messages.

    Value

    An empty internal list with the following structure:

    List of XX$info_data: List of XX
    ..$data: data.frame
    User-specified data set...$data_product_terms: data.frame
    Data set with product terms of observed variables...$n_obs: int(0)
    Number of observations...$n_var: int(0)
    Total number of variables in the data set...$var_names: chr(0)
    Names of variables.$info_model: List of XX
    ..$n_ocassions: int(0)
    Number of measurement occasions...$n_processes: int(0)
    Number of dynamic processes...$n_time_invariant int(0)
    Number of observed time-invariant variables..$linear logical(0)
    TRUE if the model is linear in observed variables...$heterogeneity chr(0)
    Specify type of unobserved heterogeneity...$use_resamples logical(0)
    . If TRUE, a resampling procedure for starting values and model diagnostics is performed...$use_open_mx logical(0)
    If TRUE, OpenMx is used, otherwise lavaan is used.$info_variables: List of XX
    ..$user_names_time_varying: char[0,0]
    User-Specified names of observed time-varying variables...$generic_names_time_varying: char[0,0]
    Generic names of observed time-varying variables...$names_processes: char[0,0]
    Names of dynamic processes...$info_time_invariant_varianbles: char[0,0]
    Names and causal structure of observed time-invariant variables...$names_time_invariant_unique: char[0,0]
    Names of unique observed time-invariant variables...$names_time_invariant_unobserved_additive: char[0,0]
    Names of UNobserved time-invariant variables...$names_time_invariant_unobserved_autoregressive: char[0,0]
    Names of UNobserved time-invariant variables...$names_time_invariant_unobserved_cross_lagged: char[0,0]
    Names of UNobserved time-invariant variables.$info_parameters: List of XX
    ..$C_table: data.frame
    Table with labeled model parameters (structural coefficients)...$Psi_table: data.frame
    Table with labeled model parameters (covariance matrix).model_matrices: List of XX
    ..$C_labels: char[0,0]
    Character matrix of labels of structural coefficients...$Psi_labels: char[0,0]
    Character matrix of labels of covariance matrix...$select_observed_only: num[0,0]
    Numeric matrix to select observed variables...$C_start: num[0,0]
    Numeric matrix of starting values of structural coefficients...$Psi_start: num[0,0]
    Numeric matrix of starting values of covariance matrix.$model_syntax: List of XX
    ..$lavaan: list
    Model specified in lavaan...$OpenMx: list
    Model specified in OpenMx.$control: List of XX
    ..$verbose: int(0)

    References

    Gische, C., West, S.G., & Voelkle, M.C. (2021) Forecasting Causal Effects of Interventions versus Predicting Future Outcomes, Structural Equation Modeling: A Multidisciplinary Journal, 28:3, 475-492, DOI: 10.1080/10705511.2020.1780598
